Carroll County is strategically located in beautiful West Georgia. We’re at the heart of, well, just about everything! Located in the nation’s #1 State for Business, Carroll County is just 45 minutes to Atlanta’s business district and the Hartsfield Jackson International Airport with direct flights to every major city in the US and key international cities. We offer superior speed to market with easy access to Interstate 20, the Savannah and Brunswick Ports, and the future West Central Inland Port. You will have crucial links to key cities throughout the US in 24 to 48-hour drives.

Our workforce is strong, talented, and growing – thanks to best-in-class preK-12 schools, a nationally recognized College and Career Academy, West Georgia Technical College, and the University of West Georgia. Our exceptional educational infrastructure is producing high-demand talent in top fields, from nursing and healthcare technology to advanced manufacturing, engineering, finance, and computing.

If you’re looking for the ideal place to grow your business in a community with a truly exceptional quality of life for your family and your associates, look West … to Carroll County. Carroll Tomorrow will be here for you every step of the way with connections, resources, and solutions. Give us a call!
